Feature: SimplePatternSemantics

  Scenario: Undirected match in self-relationship graph
    Given an empty graph
    And having executed:
      """
      CREATE (a:A)-[:LOOP]->(a)
      """
    When executing query:
      """
      MATCH p = ()--()
      RETURN p
      """
    Then the result should be:
      | p                    |
      | <(:A)-[:LOOP]->(:A)> |
    And no side effects

